	<h3>TerraPower · IT support, Tier 2</h3>
	<p>
		IT for a nuclear energy R&amp;D company operating in a compliance-heavy government-cloud
		environment. Functionally the senior technical member of the team, with no Tier 3 above.
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Active Directory and M365 administration: account lifecycle, security groups, licensing,
			auditing via Purview, Intune, and the Azure security dashboard.
		</li>
		<li>
			Took the team's PowerShell from ad-hoc one-offs to production tooling: input validation,
			dry-run modes, structured logging, error discrimination. Introduced version control and
			change review where neither existed.
		</li>
		<li>
			Lab IT support: LabVIEW experiment rigs, NI cRIO controllers, Siemens-based systems,
			scientific instruments, air-gapped machines, 24/7 uptime constraints. Ran a Purdue-model
			classification and gap analysis of lab assets.
		</li>
		<li>
			Documentation and process design: KB authorship, a Jira-based documentation
			change-management workflow, technician training paths, and a Git onboarding guide
			written for readers with zero programming background.
		</li>
		<li>Mentor one Tier 1 technician directly; wrote the training path to scale past one.</li>
	</ul>

